The '''Seattle Municipal Archives''' are the official [[archive]] of the city of [[Seattle]]. The organization is housed in [[Seattle City Hall]].
The organization was formally established in 1985.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://seattletimes.com/html/pacificnw/2011311575_pacificpdorp21.html |title=Revived Seattle Municipal Archives celebrate 25 years |first=Paul |last=Dorpat |work=seattletimes.com |date=20 March 2010 |accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref> The city of Seattle stores its city records here.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.seattlechannel.org/CityStream/segments?videoid=x21445 |title=CityStream: City Clerk's Collection |first=Feliks |last=Banel |work=seattlechannel.org |date=3 October 2013 |accessdate=18 February 2015}}</ref>
The Seattle Municipal Archive accepted a {{US$|100,000}} from the [[National Archives and Records Administration]] to process records.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.archives.gov/nhprc/projects/states-territories/wa.html |title=Washington |author=no author listed |work=archives.gov |date=n.d. |accessdate=8 February 2015}}</ref>
By 2002 many of the archives photographs from before the 1930s had begun to deteriorate and the archival budget did not allow for all of them to be digitized to contemporary quality standards for archives.<ref name="Murakami 2002">{{cite web |url= http://www.seattlepi.com/news/article/City-s-old-photographs-literally-fading-with-time-1084665.php |title=City's old photographs literally fading with time - seattlepi.com |first=Kery |last=Murakami |work=seattlepi.com |date=7 April 2002 |accessdate=18 February 2015}}</ref> At this time, the archival collection had at least been scanned, but many of the pieces were low quality, and the decision was made to prioritize 3000 of the 1,500,000 pieces in the collection for high quality [[digital preservation]].<ref name="Murakami 2002"/> Most of the archive's pictures from this time period were taken by city workers and document civil engineering.<ref name="Murakami 2002"/>
From its founding until the present, Scott Cline has served as director of the archives.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www2.kuow.org/program.php?id=16981 |title=The Seattle Municipal Archives |first=Jeannie |last=Yandel |work=www2.kuow.org |publisher=[[KUOW-FM]] |date=20 February 2009 |accessdate=18 February 2015}}</ref> Cline studied history at [[Portland State University]].<ref name="Murakami 2002"/>
