'''''The Friendly Guide to Music''''' is a 'beginner's guide' to [[classical music]], voiced by English actor and [[TV personality|presenter]] [[Tony Robinson]].  It covers the period from early music, [[Medieval music|Medieval]] and [[Renaissance music]], to the modern era, [[20th-century classical music]], [[contemporary classical music]], and [[21st-century classical music]], and its objective is to create a guide to music that is not needlessly complex.

